CICS is an app seever and transaction monitor 
that allows an app to be accessed 
interactively from a terminal 
or browser.

The tesources that CIVS needs for 
this is collectively called the
CICS region.

Each interaction through CICS 
is called a transaction, and is
facilitated through a task which 
can invoke multiple programs, 
typically written in COBOL.

Design of a terminal svreen is done using a 
facility called BMS (basic mapping support) 
and involves creating a map of 
the terminal screen in which 
are places the various artifacts such as IO fields needed for tge trandavtion.

Punters coming from a VMS background may 
equate a task with ACMS and BMS with 
DECFORMS which achieve a similar 
result. Although DECFORMS being provedural msy arguably achieve the
status of a task.

